The evidence with the title 'What caused crime to decline in the U.S.? - The Atlantic ' says Apr 15, 2016  ... In the early 1990s , U.S. crime rates had been on a steep upward climb since the Lyndon B. Johnson presidency . The crack-cocaine epidemic in the mid-1980s added fuel to the fire , and handgun-related homicides more than doubled between 1985 and 1990 . That year, murders peaked in New York City  ... 
